<p>The West End's Victorian homes typically feature steep-pitched roofs excellent for solar installations, though complex rooflines may require multiple array orientations. These larger homes often benefit from zoned HVAC systems, making ducted mini-splits or hybrid heat pump systems ideal choices. Deering Center and Oakdale neighborhoods, with more modern construction and simpler rooflines, often accommodate larger solar arrays and traditional ducted heat pump systems most easily.</p>

